House Resolution 260
By: Representative Glaize of the 67th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Sanaa Scipio; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Sanaa Scipio, an accomplished 11th-grade student at Landmark Christian
3 School in Fairburn, Georgia, has demonstrated exceptional leadership and a strong passion
4 for public policy, community service, and civic engagement; and
5 WHEREAS, Sanaa actively contributes to her school community as a member of both the
6 National Honor Society and the Impact Leadership Academy and she serves as manager of
7 her school's regional championship soccer team; and
8 WHEREAS, as further testament to her exemplary service, she established and leads
9 Landmark's Public Forum Debate Program, where she both coaches and inspires her peers;
10 and
11 WHEREAS, beyond the classroom, Sanaa has trained with the Veritas Debate Institute to
12 hone her strategic thinking skills and ability to analyze complex issues, which led to her
13 presenting a winning proposal before a panel of executive leaders at a Fortune 500 company;
14 and
