15 WHEREAS, deeply committed to civic engagement, Sanaa additionally serves on both the
16 Fairburn Youth City Council and the Fulton County Youth Commission, using her voice to
17 advocate for meaningful change while dedicating over 400 volunteer hours to community
18 service initiatives; and
19 WHEREAS, as a Hugh O'Brian Youth Leadership (HOBY) Ambassador, Sanaa has gained
20 valuable leadership experience and expanded her global perspective through study journeys
21 in Italy and Cuba as well as her participation in a Uganda Literacy Project; and
22 WHEREAS, her dedication to excellence has earned her the Congressional Award Silver
23 Medal, the President's Volunteer Service Award, and the AP Scholar recognition; and
24 WHEREAS, driven by a passion for helping others, Sanaa has dedicated her future to making
25 a positive impact in her community and beyond through shaping public policies that promote
26 justice and equality.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body recognize and commend Sanaa Scipio for her outstanding youth
29 leadership and her commitment to academic success as well as extend the most sincere best
30 wishes for future success.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Sanaa
33 Scipio.
